Definition: expressive of sympathetic pleasure or joy on account of someone's success or good fortune
Example: a congratulatory telegram; the usual congratulatory crowd was conspicuously absent; a gratulatory address
Synonyms: verb, emotion, congratulate, communication, gratulatory, expressive, of, sympathetic, pleasure, or, joy, on, account, someone, s, success, good, fortune, a, telegram, the, usual, crowd, was, conspicuously, absent, address
Category: adj.all
